o%20to%20count%20as%20an%20asset%20in%20mortgage%20lending%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sens.%20Elizabeth%20Warren%20and%20Bernie%20Sanders.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ca26241c6cc5071574eda57%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221118%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESens.%20Elizabeth%20Warren%20and%20Bernie%20Sanders.%3Cp%3EJose%20Luis%20Magana%2FAP%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20group%20of%20senators%20has%20announced%20a%20probe%20into%20FHFA%20director%20William%20Pulte's%20crypto%20plan.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPulte%20wants%20Fannie%20Mae%20and%20Freddie%20Mac%20to%20count%20crypto%20as%20an%20asset%20when%20assessing%20mortgage%20risk.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20senators%20believe%20the%20plan%20to%20be%20risky%20to%20due%20to%20crypto's%20high%20level%20of%20volatility.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20group%20of%20Democratic%20senators%20announced%20a%20probe%20of%20the%20Federal%20Housing%20Finance%20Agency%20head's%20plan%20to%20push%20Fannie%20Mae%20and%20Freddie%20Mac%20to%20count%20crypto%20as%20an%20asset%20when%20assessing%20mortgage%20risk.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20FHFA%20director%20William%20Pulte%20announced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrypto-mortgage-asset-fhfa-fannie-freddie-housing-pulte-trump-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20would%20allow%20Fannie%20Mae%20and%20Freddie%20Mac%20to%20count%20cryptocurrency%20as%20an%20asset%20in%20mortgage%20lending%20assessments%20for%20single-family%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20%3Cspan%3Emany%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fpulte%2Fstatus%2F1937944964656152800%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ERepublican%20officials%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20responded%20positively%20to%20the%20proposal%2C%20Democratic%20senators%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%20led%20by%20Jeff%20Merkley%2C%20are%20initiating%20a%20probe%20into%20Pulte's%20plan.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20group%20also%20includes%20Elizabeth%20Warren%2C%20Bernie%20Sanders%2C%20Chris%20Van%20Hollen%2C%20and%20Mazie%20K.%20Hirono.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d5354d1a-9ee4-4c18-889d-5880ed5509de%5C%22%3ERisks%20for%20home%20buyers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20FHFA%20chief%2C%20the%20senators%20requested%20further%20information%20regarding%20the%20plan.%20They%20noted%20the%20high%20volatility%20of%20crypto%20and%20cited%20statements%20from%20consumer%20advocates%20who%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2025%2F06%2F26%2Fbusiness%2Fcrypto-industry-housing-market.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpressed%20concern%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20tying%20the%20%26quot%3Blightly%20regulated%20and%20highly%20volatile%20investment%20asset%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20housing%20market%2C%20noting%20its%20importance%20to%20the%20broader%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%202008%20crisis%20proved%20that%20lax%20financial%20practices%20around%20risky%20investments%20can%20blow%20up%20the%20housing%20market%E2%80%94and%20hardworking%20families%20in%20Oregon%20and%20across%20the%20country%20paid%20the%20price.%20Crypto%20poses%20serious%20risks%20to%20the%20stability%20of%20the%20housing%20market.%20This%20is%20a%20risk%20we%20must%20address%2C%26quot%3B%20Sen.%20Merkley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20also%20references%20a%20report%20from%20Fannie%20Mae%20at%20the%20end%20of%202024%20in%20which%20it%20listed%20crypto%2C%20private%20coins%2C%20and%20stablecoins%20as%20collateral%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bleast%20appealing%20application%26quot%3B%20for%20blockchain%20technology.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20take%20aim%20at%20a%20part%20of%20Pulte's%20proposal%20that%20says%20crypto%20can%20be%20considered%20as%20an%20asset%20without%20converting%20it%20to%20dollars.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BExpanding%20underwriting%20criteria%20to%20include%20the%20consideration%20of%20unconverted%20cryptocurrency%20assets%20could%20pose%20risks%20to%20the%20stability%20of%20the%20housing%20market%20and%20the%20financial%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20letter%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20senators%20also%20highlight%20potential%20risk%20regarding%20crypto%20liquidity%2C%20referencing%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcorporatefinanceinstitute.com%2Fresources%2Fcryptocurrency%2Fliquidity-in-cryptocurrency%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Corporate%20Finance%20Institute%20that%20describes%20the%20market%20as%20%26quot%3Bfar%20from%20being%20as%20large%20and%20liquid%20as%20other%20financial%20markets%20that%20professional%20investors%20would%20normally%20participate%20in.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20flag%20the%20high%20volatility%20in%20crypto%20as%20an%20issue%20they're%20concerned%20about.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20the%20extent%20that%20historical%20volatility%20and%20liquidity%20persists%20even%20as%20the%20market%20matures%2C%20a%20borrower%20using%20crypto%20faces%20an%20increased%20risk%20that%20they%20may%20not%20be%20able%20to%20exit%20a%20crypto%20position%20and%20convert%20to%20cash%20at%20a%20price%20that%20would%20allow%20them%20to%20buffer%20against%20risk%20of%20mortgage%20default.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d8cfc345-2930-4937-80cb-b3a9c0fc7400%5C%22%3EPotential%20conflicts%20of%20interest%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20also%20includes%20concerns%20regarding%20conflicts%20of%20interest%20among%20Trump%20and%20other%20administration%20officials%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-administration-officials-investments-cryptocurrency-bitcoin-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eties%20to%20the%20crypto%20market%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20senators%20said%20such%20conflicts%20could%20%26quot%3Bunduly%20influence%20their%20proposals%26quot%3B%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20further%20po