us.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20begins%20with%20harvesting%20the%20plant%E2%80%99s%20stems%2C%20which%20are%20then%20sun-dried%20and%20boiled%20in%20an%20alkaline%20solution%20to%20break%20down%20the%20fibres.%20This%20softened%20pulp%20is%20beaten%20and%20mixed%20with%20water%20and%20a%20natural%20plant-based%20binder%20to%20create%20a%20slurry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mixture%20is%20poured%20onto%20mesh%20frames%2C%20where%20the%20water%20drains%20out%20and%20the%20thin%20layer%20of%20pulp%20is%20left%20to%20dry%20under%20the%20sun.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-media-text%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-media-text__content%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnlike%20many%20other%20small-scale%20paper%20makers%2C%20Sushmita%20does%20not%20rely%20on%20newspaper%20pulp%20to%20hold%20the%20paper%20together.%20Nor%20does%20she%20bleach%20it%20to%20make%20it%20look%20%E2%80%9Ccleaner%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20use%20only%20natural%20binders%2C%20and%20the%20paper%20retains%20its%20natural%20greenish%20tint.%20I%20believe%20the%20quality%20of%20paper%20is%20defined%20by%20how%20easy%20it%20is%20to%20write%20on%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20how%20white%20it%20looks%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20entire%20process%20is%20quick%20and%20low-cost.%20%E2%80%9CWith%201%20kg%20of%20wet%20water%20hyacinth%2C%20you%20can%20make%2030%20A4%20sheets%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20estimates.%20%E2%80%9CFrom%20harvesting%20to%20making%20the%20pulp%2C%20it%20takes%20about%2025%20minutes.%20The%20drying%20takes%20another%2045.%20With%20practice%2C%20you%20can%20do%20it%20even%20faster%20%E2%80%94%20maybe%20in%2015%20minutes.%20And%20the%20cost%20per%20sheet%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20more%20than%20Rs%202.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-media-text__media%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSu